The center is located  away from where the protesters had gathered and Belmar said he did not think the shooting was related to protests over Brown’s death.

'I don’t think it is,' he said. 'It didn’t happen within the proximity of the protest area. This is a fairly secluded area. I wouldn’t have any reason to think that it was linked in any way, shape or form.  

At the original press conference, Belmar said officers chased two suspects, and as he closed in on one of them, the second suspect pulled out a gun and fired at the officer, who was shot in one arm before returning fire. 

Officials have not released the officer’s name or said how long he had been on the police force.

Mike O'Connell, communications director for the State Emergency Management Agency, said authorities were looking for the suspect.

He said: 'A search is underway for the suspect in the shooting of the officer.' 

