Police from various different forces  responded to the scene  and set up a staging area on West Florissant Road, KMOV reported. 

Reports indicate that the suspect fled on foot into a neighborhood near West Florissant Avenue and Stein Street.

Officers and police helicopters canvassed the area in an attempt to find the shooter.

There were conflicting reports over the reason for the shooting which appears not to be linked to protests over the death of Michael Brown by a white police officer.

NBC News reported an officer interrupted a burglary at a business on Saturday night and was shot in the arm once before the suspect ran off.

